Undertake data analysis including data modelling, competitor or 3rd party product and market reviews to ensure best in class performance outcomes for Leadbolt’s products;
Produce and maintain documentation for product and data analysis including reports, specifications, implementation plans, testing/QA regimes and summarize any results as needed or requested;
Liaise within broader cross functional teams where required according to requirements of the business.
What you will bring:
Minimum of 3+ years’ professional experience
Minimum Master’s Degree in data science related discipline
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Action/outcome and performance-based mindset;
It would be awesome if you also brought:
Minimum 2+ years’ relevant experience in:
o online digital media/agency
o desktop or mobile ad serving
o performance/data science-based role
Collaborative mindset and enjoys consultation with others;
Ability to adapt multiple approaches and with a passion for problem solving;
Ability to work within a cross functional team environment;

What makes us different?
As we continue to expand globally and find the best talent out there, we are looking for innovative, ingenious, driven and revolutionary people to join us.
Working at Leadbolt gives the opportunity to work with industry experts and for you to grow your skillset and gain valuable experiences that will build and shape your career for the future.

If you can see yourself at Leadbolt and want to be part of all of this, apply now by sending us a video cover letter (tell us about yourself) and attaching your resume.

