Data Analyst – Energy Strategic Partners
Location: UK – Head Office / Newcastle

The Role
The Data Analyst is responsible for tracking and analysing trends and performance of each supplier in areas such as pricing and products, as well as reporting internal supplier KPIs eg. Sales performance, supplier mix and quality metrics such as go-live and compliance levels. This information will need to be analysed in a very detailed manner – tracking trends and observations per sales channel and customer type.

The Data Analyst will help forge new, and build existing supplier relationships by supporting the team with regular insight and direction, alongside demonstrating the financial & commercial impact of any insights gained. These insights will also be used to provide the SP&A and Operational team with recommendations and performance updates.

The Data Analyst will also be responsible for competitor and market analysis, and highlighting any new entrants or changes to competitor/supplier proposition/strategy.

The ideal candidate must be meticulous with data comparison, financial modelling and trend charting. The Partner Account Manager will also be expected to become a supplier expert and know their suppliers deeply and have a fundamental understanding of where the energy supply market is going (in terms of product, legislation, compliance, strategy, margins etc.)

Responsibilities
Market intelligence – gaining insight into supplier movement, new market entries and products;
Analysing information provided from weekly pricing comparison graphs and reporting on changes, market conditions driving prices, and impacts;
Sales performance reporting and impact modelling (against targets, commercial, cash position);
Supplier mix trend reporting and impact modelling (against targets, commercial, cash position);
Managing supplier meeting agendas, progress and supplier information decks;
Maintaining supplier and operational relationships to utilise the data analysed.
Experience
Essential

Data Analysis experience;
Demonstrated consistent success in forming and building relationships internally and externally;
Experience in creating robust, clear and articulate business plans and growth strategies, and to be able to model the impact of supplier mix shifting and new supplier onboarding;
Evidence of excellence in reporting on and monitoring account progress;
Experience in commercial modelling/impact verification.
Desirable

Ideally a working knowledge of the utilities sector, including supplier product offerings;
Experience in writing and presenting review presentations.
Personal Qualities, Aptitudes, and Skills
Refined presentation and communication skills;
Can work closely with Sales and Product Marketing to identify company needs ;
Comfortable numerically, and familiar with managing performance via KPIs, with the discipline to interrogate the data to identify trends, issues and successes from a range of sources;
Proficient in MS Office applications;
Strong work ethic is resourceful, assertive and takes initiative;
Very strong written communication skills;
Highly organised;
Excellent people and management skills to interact with staff, colleagues and cross-functional teams, and third parties;
Results-oriented, analytical, pragmatic, innovative, strategically-aware, commercially-minded self-starter.
Additional information
Proof of eligibility to work within the UK;
International travel required;
Willing to travel occasionally for supplier meetings.
To apply for this position, please send your CV and a covering email to recruitment@utilitywise.com.

The Company
As one of the UK’s leading business utilities consultancies, Utilitywise advises c.40,000 customers, helping them get the most value from their utilities through better procurement and efficiency services.

Having grown from a start-up business in 2006 to managing an effective IPO in 2012, Utilitywise understands the needs and concerns of all businesses, regardless of their size or sector. The plc works with clients ranging from James Whyte Joiner to the University of Bradford.

Utilitywise aims to debunk the myths that exist around utilities and support businesses across the UK to spend less time worrying about utilities so they can spend more time running their companies. In 2016 Utilitywise was named an OEM partner by Dell as part of a joint strategy to introduce Internet of Things (IoT) Building Automation solutions to customers.

Utilitywise is a UK company quoted on the AIM market of the London Stock Exchange. In 2017, Utilitywise was named as one of the top 1000 Companies to Inspire Britain by the London Stock Exchange in its annual celebration of some of the fastest-growing and most dynamic small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in the UK.

