About the role:
The Senior Business Analyst is responsible for analysis, requirements gathering, selection, development and delivery of integrated solutions for large and complex programs and Projects within Client. The position works with both internal and external delivery partners within the Client Digital Technology & Innovation (DTI). This position directly reports to the Project Manager.
Job Description:
Drive the design, documentation and development of business requirements and functional specifications using context diagram and process models;
Elicit and document user requirements using various techniques which include but not limited to interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, surveys, business process descriptions, use cases, scenarios, business analysis, task and workflow analysis;
Evaluate proposed system solutions in close liaison with system developers to ensure delivery of solutions is consistent with Client expectations;
Prepare system and user acceptance test plans and scripts and work with the Test Manager to ensure delivery of quality systems that meet Client expectations;
Review and analyse business processes, re-engineer as necessary to improve efficiency, effectiveness and/or usability using strategic analysis techniques and process models;
Assist in the production of a robust business case that includes options analyzed, impact assessments and funding recommendations where required;
Manage and develop relationships with project team members and stakeholders in order to ensure successful projects outcomes and to maintain client satisfaction;
